      <p>A monitor should sit at eye level. Most desks are too low for a 24-inch monitor to reach that height, which forces you to look down and hunch — and within a week, your neck and upper back will let you know. A riser fixes your posture instantly for under $35, and the storage underneath converts the dead space below your screen into a home for your keyboard, mouse, and the sticky notes currently cluttering your surface. We evaluated six risers based on their specifications and design features to find which ones combine real ergonomic lift with usable storage and zero wobble.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 6 monitor riser models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For lift we assessed manufacturer-published lift height and platform dimensions. For stability we evaluated weight capacity ratings, construction material (MDF, metal, plastic), and design features that resist deflection. For storage we assessed drawer specifications and capacity based on manufacturer documentation.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Lift height accuracy and ergonomic benefit</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Load capacity, material rigidity, and drawer durability</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Storage utility, cable management, and assembly</li>
      </ul>

